DAMATURU – Nigeria Association of Road Transport Owners (NARTO), Potiskum unit in Yobe State have appealed to Anambra State government to consider the full compensation to the owner of the truck with registration number TO 168 YB carrying cows which was set ablaze by suspected gunmen at about 8:30am on Sunday 8th May, 2022. Alhaji Manga Mohammed, Chairman NARTO Potiskum made the plea today while speaking with our Correspondent on the incident. According to him “our members are performing their legitimate business of transportation to the southern parts of the country, why should they be attacked and harassed, Nigeria is our Country that we should live peacefully with one another.” -Advertisement- “We on behalf of the Association calling on Anambra State government to compensate Lawan Tukur, the owner of the burnt trailer truck in order to reduce the hardship posed on him. This truck is carrying a legal commodity and meant to improve the economy of Anambra State.”